reviews.review_text:
Significant AUD upgrade, HUGE UNDERRATED SHOW Seriously, from practically the archive's opening bell folks have praised the 10363 AUD of this monster concert. Considering the SBD every bit of that praise was warranted, as if nothing else, it breathed life into the recording, which allowed all of us listening now to get an idea of what a totally scorching smoke show we've got here.

I was going through all the stand-alone Franklin's Towers and came to this show, which I knew to have a particularly euphoria laced version from "Listen to the music play" on. Up to that point all signs pointed to strong but standard, then Jerry finds a thick vein of inspiration and the whole band lose themselves in it as well. Franklin's latter half is repeatedly wonderful. But I digress.

I noticed the un-reviewed Bob Wagner AUDs (Charlie/SirMick remastered) and couldn't resist. But I was in no way prepared to be totally blown away by the upgrade this represents. Simply put, they F'n nailed it. This AUD is crackling throughout. Sparks fly all over the place...and that is just the recording.

9/1/79 ought to be one of the most beloved shows of them all. It is totally stuffed, overflowing, and busted its sides with tasty GD.

Half-Step is kind of a throw away. Until the post Rio-Grande jam, which is an electrifying throwdown. I've already spoken to the Franklin's. Not a hard 10, but a 9+ for sure.  Get this though, Big River, FotD, LL Rain, Scarlet>Fire, Wharf Rat, and Good Lovin all possess show stopping moments that will have you coming back for the rest of your life once you've tasted it once.
